Notebook[{
  Cell["FFTLog Real-Space Matter Master Integrals", "Title"],
  Cell["This notebook is the entry point of the Gaussian FFTLog suite. It follows arXiv:1708.08130 for the scalar master integral and the reduced one-loop matter coefficients, then checks those closed forms against the local `pt_matrix/real_space/gauss` contract used by the Mathematica package.", "Text"],
  Cell["Setup", "Section"],
  Cell["Get[FileNameJoin[{NotebookDirectory[], \"FFTLog_RealSpace_Matter_MasterIntegrals.wl\"}]]", "Input"],
  Cell["Inspect The Scalar Master", "Section"],
  Cell["$RealSpaceMatterPaper", "Input"],
  Cell["MatterScalarMaster[nu1, nu2] // TraditionalForm", "Input"],
  Cell["Inspect Symmetries And Recursions", "Section"],
  Cell["MatterIdentitySummary[10]", "Input"],
  Cell["MatterIdentityNumericResidualSummary[]", "Input"],
  Cell["Inspect The Reduced One-Loop Coefficients", "Section"],
  Cell["MatterReducedKernelExpression[\"13_dd\"] // TraditionalForm", "Input"],
  Cell["MatterReducedKernelExpression[\"22_dd\"] // TraditionalForm", "Input"],
  Cell["MatterReferenceKernelExpression[\"13_dd\"] // TraditionalForm", "Input"],
  Cell["MatterReferenceKernelExpression[\"22_dd\"] // TraditionalForm", "Input"],
  Cell["Exact Symbolic Checks", "Section"],
  Cell["MatterKernelValidationSummary[10]", "Input"],
  Cell["Fast Rational Spot Checks", "Section"],
  Cell["MatterKernelNumericResidualSummary[]", "Input"],
  Cell["Inspect Any Nonzero Residual Explicitly", "Section"],
  Cell["AssociationMap[MatterKernelValidationExpression, $RealSpaceMatterKernelNames]", "Input"],
  Cell["Local CLASS-PT Reference Checks", "Section"],
  Cell["$ClassPTMatterDefaults", "Input"],
  Cell["Table[<|\"Nmax\" -> n, \"M13Reference\" -> LocalClassPTReferencePath[\"M13\", n], \"M22Reference\" -> LocalClassPTReferencePath[\"M22\", n], \"M13Output\" -> LocalNotebookEvaluationPath[\"M13\", n], \"M22Output\" -> LocalNotebookEvaluationPath[\"M22\", n]|>, {n, {128, 256, 512}}]", "Input"],
  Cell["LocalNotebookEvaluationComparison[\"M13\", 128]", "Input"],
  Cell["LocalNotebookEvaluationComparison[\"M22\", 128]", "Input"],
  Cell["LocalNotebookEvaluationComparison[\"M13\", 256]", "Input"],
  Cell["LocalNotebookEvaluationComparison[\"M22\", 256]", "Input"],
  Cell["LocalNotebookEvaluationComparison[\"M13\", 512]", "Input"],
  Cell["LocalNotebookEvaluationComparison[\"M22\", 512]", "Input"],
  Cell["AssociationThread[{128, 256, 512}, ExportLocalNotebookEvaluationTables /@ {128, 256, 512}]", "Input"],
  Cell["Notes", "Section"],
  Cell["The scalar master `I(nu1,nu2)` is the universal analytic object in the FFTLog reduction. The local kernel text files store the reduced coefficient functions used by the package-side contractions, so this notebook validates those reduced coefficients directly while keeping the scalar master visible as the organizing object. The local pt_matrices files are used only as a final comparison layer. For M22 at N=256, the correct CLASS-PT runtime reference is the packed file M22oneline_N256_packed_CLASS-PTreference.dat rather than the plain M22oneline_N256_CLASS-PTreference.dat.", "Text"]
  },
 WindowSize -> {1200, 900},
 WindowMargins -> {{Automatic, 100}, {Automatic, 40}},
 StyleDefinitions -> "Default.nb"
]
